<topic id='business_definition_hospital_provider_spell.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Hospital Provider Spell - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider_spell">Hospital Provider Spell</xref>
 is an 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity_group">ACTIVITY GROUP</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider_spell">Hospital Provider Spell</xref>
 is the total continuous stay of a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 using a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_bed">Hospital Bed</xref>
 on premises controlled by a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_health_care_provider">Health Care Provider</xref>
 during which medical care is the responsibility of one or more 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_consultant">CONSULTANTS</xref>, or the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 is receiving care under one or more 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nursing_episode">Nursing Episodes</xref>
 or 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_midwife_episode">Midwife Episodes</xref>
 in a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_ward">WARD</xref>. During 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nursing_episode">Nursing Episodes</xref>
 and 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_midwife_episode">Midwife Episodes</xref>
 general medical care is the responsibility of their own 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_general_medical_practitioner">GENERAL MEDICAL PRACTITIONER</xref>, who is not acting as a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_consultant">CONSULTANT</xref>. The 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider_spell">Hospital Provider Spell</xref>
 may be as a result of an 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_elective_admission_list_entry">ELECTIVE ADMISSION LIST ENTRY</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
During the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider_spell">Hospital Provider Spell</xref>, the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 may be subject to more than one 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_administrative_category_period">ADMINISTRATIVE CATEGORY PERIODS</xref>. The 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 may be subject to one or more 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_critical_care_period">CRITICAL CARE PERIODS</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider_spell">Hospital Provider Spell</xref>
 starts when a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_consultant">CONSULTANT</xref>, 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_nurse">NURSE</xref>
 or 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_midwife">MIDWIFE</xref>
 assumes responsibility for care following the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_decision_to_admit">DECISION TO ADMIT</xref>
 the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>. This may be before formal admission procedures have been completed and the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 transferred to a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_ward">WARD</xref>. For example, if a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 is brought into hospital as an emergency and dies in the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_operating_theatre">OPERATING THEATRE</xref>
 before being transferred to a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_ward">WARD</xref>, the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 would have started a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider_spell">Hospital Provider Spell</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
In some circumstances a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 may take 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_home_leave">Home Leave</xref>, or 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_mental_health_leave_of_absence">Mental Health Leave of Absence</xref>
 for a period of 28 days or less, or have a current period of 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_mental_health_absence_without_leave">Mental Health Absence Without Leave</xref>
 of 28 days or less, which does not interrupt the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider_spell">Hospital Provider Spell</xref>, 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_consultant_episode__hospital_provider_">Consultant Episode (Hospital Provider)</xref>, 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nursing_episode">Nursing Episode</xref>, 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_midwife_episode">Midwife Episode</xref>
 or 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_stay">Hospital Stay</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
Each admission as part of a series of regular day/night admissions generates a separate 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider_spell">Hospital Provider Spell</xref>
 and 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_consultant_episode__hospital_provider_">Consultant Episode (Hospital Provider)</xref>. An admission is the start of the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>'s 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider_spell">Hospital Provider Spell</xref>
 and the first 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_consultant_episode__hospital_provider_">Consultant Episodes (Hospital Provider)</xref>, 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_midwife_episode">Midwife Episode</xref>
 or 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nursing_episode">Nursing Episode</xref>
 within the spell. If the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 is on a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_site">Hospital Site</xref>
 the admission will also start the first 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_stay">Hospital Stay</xref>
 and, unless the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 has to spend time as a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_lodged_patient">LODGED PATIENT</xref>, the admission will also start the first 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_ward_stay">Ward Stay</xref>
 within that 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider_spell">Hospital Provider Spell</xref>. If the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 is in a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_care_home">Care Home</xref>
 the admission will start the first 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_care_home_stay__consultant_care_">Care Home Stay (Consultant Care)</xref>
 within the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider_spell">Hospital Provider Spell</xref>. Any admission of a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_person">PERSON</xref>
 liable to be detained under the Mental Health Act 1983 cannot be in a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_care_home">Care Home</xref>
 and must be a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider_spell">Hospital Provider Spell</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
A discharge will be the end of the last 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_consultant_episode__hospital_provider_">Consultant Episode (Hospital Provider)</xref>, 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_midwife_episode">Midwife Episode</xref>
 or 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nursing_episode">Nursing Episode</xref>, and the end of the last 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_care_home_stay__consultant_care_">Care Home Stay (Consultant Care)</xref>
 or 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_stay">Hospital Stay</xref>
 and 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_ward_stay">Ward Stay</xref>
 within that 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider_spell">Hospital Provider Spell</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
If there is any time spent as a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_lodged_patient">LODGED PATIENT</xref>
 before transfer to a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_ward">WARD</xref>
 this is included in the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider_spell">Hospital Provider Spell</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider_spell">Hospital Provider Spell</xref>
 starts with a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider">Hospital Provider</xref>
 admission and ends with a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider">Hospital Provider</xref>
 discharge.        </p>
      <p>
There may be one or more 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_mental_health_delayed_discharge_period">Mental Health Delayed Discharge Periods</xref>
 recorded for any 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_consultant_episode__hospital_provider_">Consultant Episode (Hospital Provider)</xref>
 within the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider_spell">Hospital Provider Spell</xref>.        </p>
